Service Level Agreements (SLAs) define Microsoft’s uptime commitments for Azure services.

For example:

* 99.9% uptime
* 99.99% uptime

SLAs influence architecture decisions.

For example, deploying across availability zones may improve SLA coverage.

A real-life use case is mission-critical enterprise apps.

Another example is designing resilient SaaS platforms.

SLAs guide reliability expectations and architectural planning.
